          <details class="group py-6">
            <summary class="flex items-center justify-between cursor-pointer list-none font-brand text-lg font-medium text-navy dark:text-white">
              What does "BYO keys" mean?
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-storm dark:text-white/60 group-open:rotate-45 transition-transform" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M12 4.5v15m7.5-7.5h-15" />
              </svg>
            </summary>
            <p class="mt-4 text-storm dark:text-white/60 leading-relaxed">
              Bring Your Own Keys. You connect your own API key from providers like OpenAI, Anthropic (Claude), Google Gemini, Groq, or others. You pay the provider directly for what you use. Flow never sees your key — it's encrypted on your device. You can also use Ollama to run AI models entirely on your machine with zero external calls.
            </p>
          </details>

          <details class="group py-6">
            <summary class="flex items-center justify-between cursor-pointer list-none font-brand text-lg font-medium text-navy dark:text-white">
              Is my data really private?
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-storm dark:text-white/60 group-open:rotate-45 transition-transform" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M12 4.5v15m7.5-7.5h-15" />
              </svg>
            </summary>
            <p class="mt-4 text-storm dark:text-white/60 leading-relaxed">
              Yes. The desktop app stores everything in a local SQLite database on your machine. There is zero telemetry, zero analytics, and zero tracking. We cannot see your data. When you use AI features, your conversations go directly to the provider you chose — Flow acts as a passthrough, not a data collector.
            </p>
          </details>

          <details class="group py-6">
            <summary class="flex items-center justify-between cursor-pointer list-none font-brand text-lg font-medium text-navy dark:text-white">
              Does it work offline?
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-storm dark:text-white/60 group-open:rotate-45 transition-transform" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M12 4.5v15m7.5-7.5h-15" />
              </svg>
            </summary>
            <p class="mt-4 text-storm dark:text-white/60 leading-relaxed">
              The desktop app works 100% offline for all core features — journal, tasks, calendar, routines, projects, and vault. AI features require an internet connection to reach your provider's API, unless you run Ollama locally. Search is powered by SQLite FTS5 and works offline.
            </p>
          </details>

          <details class="group py-6">
            <summary class="flex items-center justify-between cursor-pointer list-none font-brand text-lg font-medium text-navy dark:text-white">
              Can I export my data?
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-storm dark:text-white/60 group-open:rotate-45 transition-transform" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M12 4.5v15m7.5-7.5h-15" />
              </svg>
            </summary>
